<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.1123L25/32</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 240</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 866,
                            of the 22nd ultimo, in which you enclose a copy of a note addressed by
                            you to the Panaman Foreign Office urging more energetic action on the
                            part of the Panaman authorities in the investigation of the riot which
                            took place in the city of Colon on April 2, 1915.</p>
                        <p>You also report the result of your conferences with Senor Lefevre with
                            the same end in view.</p>
                        <p>Your action in the matter is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. Osborne</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>